body: @collinarnett, it is because onnx.shape_inference.infer_shapes doesn't support model > 2G. Will make a fix.
Hey I was just wondering if there was a status update on this. I am currently blocked on my project because of this issue.
It is in our backlog. Will try fixing the issue this week.

Are there any updates regarding the issue?
I am also trying to convert DialoGPT-large model to onnx,

```
python -m onnxruntime.transformers.convert_to_onnx \
        -m model_path \
        --model_class GPT2LMHeadModel \
        --output output_path \
        --use_external_data_format \
        -p fp16 \
        --optimize_onnx \
        --use_gpu
```

The output of the script is the following:
```
PyTorch Version:1.9.0a0+2ecb2c7
Transformers Version:4.6.1
Onnxruntime Version:1.8.0
....
  File "/opt/conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/onnxconverter_common/float16.py", line 130, in convert_float_to_float16
    model = func_infer_shape(model)
  File "/opt/conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/onnx/shape_inference.py", line 34, in infer_shapes
    model_str = model.SerializeToString()
ValueError: Message onnx.ModelProto exceeds maximum protobuf size of 2GB: 3391372453
```

The conversion works when I comment the line 130 in `onnxconverter_common/float16.py` script, but the quality of the generation of the converted model is noticeably lower.
I met the same problems while quantizating the mBart model (about 3GB)

We just added an option in quantization to disable shapeinference in quantization, which is not necessary for dynamic_quantization. You can enable this option to solve this issue: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/60089f7093e4e26f837be4bbf74d38cb97b43e4b/onnxruntime/python/tools/quantization/quantize.py#L189
How come there is such a drastic difference in logits when shape inference is turned off as I referenced in #6549? @yufenglee

I don't think it is related to shape inference. To confirm this, could you try calling this API to do shape inference before calling quantizatize_dynamic: https://github.com/onnx/onnx/blob/5515769e1950ce0bcf5f75cfc336a5c96a56b798/docs/PythonAPIOverview.md#shape-inference-a-large-onnx-model-2gb? 
Quantization can introduce accuracy loss. For very large model, the accuracy loss can be aggregated. 

`onnx.shape_inference.infer_shapes_path('path/to/the/model.onnx', 'output/inferred/model.onnx')`
